# Biogrix Frontend Rules

## Structure

- `frontend/apps/web` → Public website (Next.js)
- `frontend/apps/admin` → Admin dashboard (Next.js)
- `frontend/shared/ui` → Reusable UI components
- `frontend/shared/utils` → Frontend utilities

## Component Rules

- Use **functional React components** only (no class components)
- Extract reusable components into `frontend/shared/ui`
- Apps import shared components from `shared/ui`; do not duplicate
- Keep components focused; split large components into smaller ones

## Next.js Conventions

- Follow Next.js App Router or Pages Router conventions as configured
- Use file-based routing (pages or app directory)
- Prefer server components where appropriate; use client components when interactivity is needed

## Styling

- Use **TailwindCSS** for all styling
- Avoid inline styles; use Tailwind utility classes
- Prefer Tailwind over custom CSS; add custom styles only when Tailwind cannot handle the case

## Clean Component Structure

- One component per file when possible
- Co-locate component-specific styles or utilities
- Use descriptive component and file names (PascalCase for components)
